The paper deals with information-theoretic definitions and results for analyzing symmetric-key encryption schemes, which falls under the scope of information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of list-source codes and rate-distortion theory, which are relevant to coding theory (cs.CC) and signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper mentions the application of the methods in key distribution, storage, and privacy, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM) in terms of secure storage and transmission of multimedia data.
